---
const chapter = {
  number: 1,
  title: "Introduction to GFS"
};

const components = [
  {
    title: "Master Server",
    description: "The brain of GFS that manages metadata and coordinates all system operations",
    details: [
      "Maintains file system metadata",
      "Manages chunk lease assignments",
      "Handles namespace operations",
      "Coordinates system-wide activities"
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "Chunk Servers",
    description: "The workhorses that store and manage actual data chunks",
    details: [
      "Store 64MB chunks of file data",
      "Handle data replication",
      "Perform chunk operations",
      "Report status to master regularly"
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "Clients",
    description: "Applications that interact with GFS for data operations",
    details: [
      "Communicate with master for metadata",
      "Interact directly with chunk servers for data",
      "Cache metadata for better performance",
      "Handle data flow operations"
    ]
  }
];

const keyFeatures = [
  {
    title: "Scalability",
    points: [
      "Handles thousands of machines efficiently",
      "Manages petabytes of data",
      "Supports millions of operations daily"
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "Reliability",
    points: [
      "Multiple replicas for each chunk",
      "Automatic failure detection",
      "Self-healing through replication"
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "Performance",
    points: [
      "High sustained bandwidth",
      "Optimized for large files",
      "Efficient parallel operations"
    ]
  }
];
---

<div class="page">
  <h2 class="chapter-title">{chapter.number}. {chapter.title}</h2>
  
  <div class="intro-section">
    <p class="highlight-quote">
      "The Google File System (GFS) is a scalable distributed file system designed to meet Google's rapidly growing demands for data processing. It provides fault tolerance while running on inexpensive commodity hardware, and delivers high aggregate performance to a large number of clients."
    </p>

    <div class="system-overview">
      <h3>üåê System Architecture Overview</h3>
      <p>GFS revolutionized distributed storage by introducing a architecture that could handle massive scale while maintaining simplicity. The system consists of three main components working in harmony:</p>
      
      {components.map(component => (
        <div class="component-card">
          <h4>{component.title}</h4>
          <p class="component-desc">{component.description}</p>
          <ul class="component-details">
            {component.details.map(detail => (
              <li>{detail}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="interaction-flow">
      <h3>üîÑ Component Interactions</h3>
      <div class="flow-steps">
        <div class="flow-step">
          <span class="step-number">1</span>
          <p>Client contacts Master Server for metadata</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step">
          <span class="step-number">2</span>
          <p>Master returns chunk locations</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step">
          <span class="step-number">3</span>
          <p>Client communicates directly with Chunk Servers</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step">
          <span class="step-number">4</span>
          <p>Data flows between Client and Chunk Servers</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="key-features">
      <h3>üéØ Key Features</h3>
      {keyFeatures.map(feature => (
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h4>{feature.title}</h4>
          <ul>
            {feature.points.map(point => (
              <li>{point}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="real-world-impact">
      <h3>üí´ Real-World Impact</h3>
      <p>GFS has been instrumental in powering Google's core services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Powers Google Search's massive index processing</li>
        <li>Handles YouTube's vast video storage needs</li>
        <li>Supports Gmail's email storage system</li>
        <li>Enables Google Cloud Storage services</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
